name: Aluminum, Dithionite Citrate Extractable
description: Dithionite citrate extractable aluminum is an indicator of the amount of aluminum substituted for iron in iron oxides. It does not necessarily represent total pedogenic Al.

name: Aluminum, Element Mehlich3 Extractable
description: The aluminum extracted by the Mehlich III solution.

name: Aluminum, KCl Extractable
description: KCl extractable aluminum approximates the exchangeable Al, and is a measure of the active acidity present in soils with a 1:1 water pH less than 5.5. It relates to the immediate lime requirement and the CEC of the soil.

name: Aluminum, Major Element
description: Total Al is the aluminum measured after total dissolution of a size fraction of soil material. It is stored as percent of the element and reported as  percent oxide on the base of the size fraction used.

name: Aluminum, Major Element XRF

name: Aluminum, Oxalate Extractable

name: Aluminum, Sodium Pyrophosphate Extractable
description: Sodium pyrophosphate extractable aluminum is the fraction extracted by 0.1M sodium pyrophosphate. It was originally considered the portion associated with organic compounds, although subsequent evidence indicates other forms are also removed.

name: Aluminum, Total

description: Bulk density, oven dry (105 C) is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume measured on oven dry (105 C) natural fabric (clods). It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter on a <2 mm base.

name: Bulk Density, 1/3 Bar, Before Rewet (Organic Soils)
description: Bulk density, 1/3 bar rewet (organic soils) is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume being measured after samples have been equilibrated at 1/3 bar water tension, air dried, and re-equilibrated at 1/3 bar tension.

name: Bulk Density, 1/3 Bar, Estimated
description: Bulk density, 1/3 bar is estimated when no measured value exists. It has been estimated from rupture resistance, particle size distribution, and organic carbon.

name: Bulk Density, 1/3 Bar, Rewet (Organic Soils)
description: Bulk density, 1/3 bar rewet (organic soils) is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume being measured after samples have been equilibrated at 1/3 bar water tension, air dried, and re-equilibrated at 1/3 bar tension.

name: Bulk Density, Clod, Field Water Content
description: Bulk density, <2mm fraction, moist is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume measured at field (sampling) moisture on natural clods. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter on a <2 mm base.

name: Bulk Density, Compliant Cavity, Field Moisture
description: Bulk density (compliant cavity at field H20) is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume measured at field (sampling) moisture content by the compliant cavity method. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter on a <2 mm base.

name: Bulk Density, Core, <2 mm fraction, Field Moist
description: Bulk density, <2mm fraction, field moist is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume measured at field (sampling) moisture. Measurements are made on known volume cores. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter, <2 mm base.

name: Bulk Density, Field Core, Field Moisture
description: Bulk density (field core at field H20) is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume measured at field (sampling) moisture content by the field core method. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter on a <2 mm base.

name: Bulk Density, Syringe, Field Moisture
description: Bulk density (syringe at field H20) is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume measured at field (sampling) moisture content by the syringe method. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter on a <2 mm base.

name: Bulk Density, Whole Soil, Field Moist
description: Bulk density, whole soil, field moist, is the weight per unit volume of the whole soil, with volume measured at field (sampling) moisture content by the balloon method. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter, on a whole soil base.

name: Bulk Density, Whole Soil, Moist
description: Bulk density, whole soil, moist is the weight per unit volume of the whole soil, with volume measured at field (sampling) moisture in clods. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter, whole soil base.

name: C, CO3
description: The carbon content based on presence of carbonates measured by CO2 evolution after acid treatment.

name: C, glucose
description: The carbon content based on glucose calibration.

name: C, KMnO4 extract

name: CaCO3, <20 mm

description: The calcium extracted by the Mehlich III solution.

name: Calcium, Major Element

name: Calcium, Major Element XRF
description: Total Ca is the calcium measured after total dissolution of a size fraction of soil material. It is stored as elemental percent and reported as percent oxide on the base of the size fraction used.

name: Calcium, Neutral Salt Extractable
description: The neutral salt extractable calcium is the fraction removed by 1.0N NH4Cl.

name: Calcium, NH4OAc Extractable
description: NH4OAC extractable calcium is the fraction removed by pH 7.0 NH4OAC. It is assumed to represent the exchangeable Ca. It is reported as meq per 100 grams on a <2 mm base. It is not reported for samples containing carbonates or soluble salts.

name: Calcium, NH4OAc Extractable, 2M KCl displacement
description: NH4OAC extractable calcium is the fraction removed by pH 7.0 NH4OAC. It is assumed to represent the exchangeable Ca. It is reported as meq per 100 grams on a <2 mm base. It is not reported for samples containing carbonates or soluble salts.

name: Calcium, Saturation Extract
description: Calcium in the saturation extract is the fraction removed from a sample by saturating the sample with distilled H2O, then vacuum extracting the water. It is reported as meq per liter of extract.

name: Calcium, Total
description: Total Ca is the calcium measured after total dissolution of a size fraction of soil material. It is stored as elemental percent and reported as percent oxide on the base of the size fraction used.

name: Calcium, Water
description: Calcium in the water sample.

name: Calcium, Water Element
description: Total Ca is the calcium measured in the water sample.

name: Calcium, Water Extractable
description: The calcium extracted by the Water solution.

name: Calcium, X-Ray Flourescence Element
description: Calcium as determined using portable X-Ray fluorescence on a powdered sample; XRF sample cup with polypropylene film.

name: Linear Extensibility, 1/10 Bar to Ovendry, Whole Soil
description: Linear extensibility percent, whole soil, 1/10 bar/OD is the percent change in a clod dimension resulting from a water content change from oven dry to 1/10 bar tension. It is reported as percent length change on a whole soil base.

name: Linear Extensibility, 1/3 Bar to Ovendry, <2mm
description: Linear extensibility percent, <2mm, 1/3 bar/OD is the percent dimensional change of a clod as water content changes from oven dry to 1/3 bar water tension. It is reported as percent length change on a<2 mm base.

name: Linear Extensibility, 1/3 Bar to Ovendry, Rewet
description: Linear extensibility percent, rewet, 1/3 bar/OD isthe percent dimensional change of a rewet clod as water content changes from oven dry to 1/3 bar tension. It is reported as percent length change on a<2 mm base.

name: Linear Extensibility, 1/3 Bar to Ovendry, Whole Soil
description: Linear extensibility percent, whole soil, 1/3 bar/OD is the percent change in a clod dimension as water content changes from oven dry to 1/3 bar water tension. It is reported as percent length change on a whole soil base.

name: Linear Extensibility, 1/3 to 15 Bar, <2mm
description: Linear extensibility percent, <2 mm, 1/3 bar/15 bar is the percent change in a clod dimension as water content changes from 15 bar to 1/3 bar water tension. It is reported as percent length change on a <2 mm base.

name: Linear Extensibility, 1/3 to 15 Bar, Whole Soil
description: Linear extensibility percent, whole soil,1/3 bar/15 bar is the percent change in a clod dimension as water content changes from 15 bar to 1/3 bar tension. It is reported as percent length change on a whole soil base.

name: Linear Extensibility, Field Moist To Ovendry
description: Linear extensibility percent, field moist to ovendry is the percent change in a clod dimension as water content changes from oven dry to field moist water tension. It is reported as percent length change on a <2 mm base.

name: Liquid Limit, Atterberg
description: Atterberg liquid limit is the gravimetric percent water content of the soil at a defined boundary between the liquid and plastic states. It is determined by ASTM method D 4318 and reported as percent water on a <0.4 mm base.

name: pH, Oxidized (sulfidic)
description: The oxidized pH is the pH of a sample measured after incubation while saturated with distilled water. It is normally used to indicate the acid producing potential of acid sulfate materials.

name: pH, Saturated Paste

name: pH, Water
description: The pH, is the pH of the water sample.

name: pH, Water Extract

description: The phosphorus extractable by citric acid is an indicator of available phosphorus in the sample, reported as milligrams per kilogram on a <2 mm base.

name: Phosphorus, Element Mehlich3 Extractable
description: The phosphorus extracted by the Mehlich III solution.

name: Phosphorus, Ground/Water
description: The phosphorus found in a water sample. It represents the P concentration in the water, i.e. the mobile P.

name: Phosphorus, Major Element
description: Total P is the phosphorus measured after total dissolution of a size fraction of soil material. It is stored as elemental percent and reported as percent oxide on the base of the size fraction used.

name: Phosphorus, Major Element XRF
description: Total P is the phosphorus measured after total dissolution of a size fraction of soil material. It is stored as elemental percent and reported as percent oxide on the base of the size fraction used.

name: Phosphorus, Mehlich3 Extractable
description: The phosphorus extracted by the Mehlich III solution.

name: Phosphorus, New Zealand P Retention
description: The New Zealand phosphorus retention is the gravimetric percent phosphorus removed from a solution by equilibration with a sample. It is reported on a <2 mm base. High P retention indicates andic material.

name: Phosphorus, Olsen Extractable
description: The Olsen extractable phosphorus is used as an indicator of available phosphorus in calcareous soil materials (pH >6).

name: Phosphorus, Oxalate Extractable
description: Phosphorus extracted with ammonium oxalate

name: Phosphorus, Total
description: Total P is the phosphorus measured after total dissolution of a size fraction of soil material. It is stored as elemental percent and reported as percent oxide on the base of the size fraction used.

name: Phosphorus, Trace Element
description: Total P is the phosphorus measured after total dissolution of a size fraction of soil material. It is stored as elemental percent and reported as percent oxide on the base of the size fraction used.

name: Phosphorus, Water Element
description: Total P is the phosphorus measured in the water sample.

name: Phosphorus, Water Extractable
description: The phosphorus extracted by the Water solution.

name: Phosphorus, Water Soluble
description: The water soluble phosphorus is the fraction extracted by distilled water. It represents an attempt to approximate the P concentration in the soil solution, i.e. the mobile P.

name: Ratio, 15 Bar Water to Clay, <2mm
description: The ratio of 15 bar H2O percent / clay percent is calculated by (W15AD or W15FM)/CLAY_TOT, reported as grams per gram, on a <2 mm base. It provides inferences about clay mineralogy and the effectiveness of dispersion in the particle size analysis.

name: Ratio, 15 Bar Water to Clay, <2mm, Moist
description: The ratio of 15 bar H2O percent / clay percent is calculated by (W15AD or W15FM)/CLAY_TOT, reported as grams per gram, on a <2 mm base. It provides inferences about clay mineralogy and the effectiveness of dispersion in the particle size analysis.

name: Ratio, Air-dry/Ovendry
description: Airdry/ovendry H2O ratio is the ratio of air dry gravimetric percent water over oven dry (105 degrees C) gravimetric percent water. If gypsum is present, this ratio is corrected for crystal water in the gypsum.

name: Ratio, Carbon to Nitrogen

name: Ratio, Carbon to Nitrogen, MIN

name: Ratio, Carbon to Nitrogen, POM

name: Volume, >2mm, Weighted Average
description: Weighted average total clay content for control section depths

name: Volume, CEC, NH4Cl Syringe Extract
description: The volume of the extract contained in the syrringe of the CEC procedure. This value is not normally reported.  It is used in the calculation of extractable bases (Ca, Mg, Na, K).

name: Volume, CEC, NH4OAc, Syringe Extract
description: The volume of the extract contained in the syrringe of the CEC procedure. This value is not normally reported.  It is used in the calculation of extractable bases (Ca, Mg, Na, K).

name: Volume, CEC, NH4OAc, Syringe Extract, 2M KCl displacement
description: The volume of the extract contained in the syrringe of the CEC procedure. This value is not normally reported.  It is used in the calculation of extractable bases (Ca, Mg, Na, K).

name: Water Content, Bulk Sample
description: The gravimetric percent water of the bulk sample at the time of sample preparation.  This is analyte is an estimate of the field water content of the soil, if no measurement is available.

name: Water Content, Saturated Paste
description: Water content of the saturation paste is the gravimetric percent water in a sample prior to collection of the saturation extract.

name: Water Retention Difference, 1/10 to 15 Bar, Whole Soil
description: WRD-whole soil 1/10 to 15 bar is the volume of water released when the soil is dried from 1/10 bar to 15 bars water tension. It is reported as centimeters of water per centimeter depth of soil, but the value is constant for other units.

name: Water Retention Difference, 1/3 to 15 Bar, <2mm
description: The water retention difference, <2 mm is the volume fraction of water released between 1/3 and 15 bar tensions, reported as inches of water per inch of soil, on a <2 mm base.

name: Water Retention Difference, 1/3 to 15 Bar, Whole Soil
description: WRD-whole soil 1/3 bar to 15 bar is the volume of water released when the soil is dried from 1/3 bar to 15 bars water tension. It is reported as centimeters of water per centimeter depth of soil, but the value is constant for other units.

name: Water Retention, 0.06 Bar, <2mm Clod
description: 0.06 bar water, <2mm fraction of clods is the gravimetric percent water held by clods equilibrated at 0.06 bar water tension. It is reported on a <2 mm base.

name: Water Retention, 0.06 Bar, <2mm Sieve
description: 0.06 bar water, <2mm fraction is the gravimetric percent water held by <2 mm samples equilibrated at 0.06 bar water tension. It is reported on a <2 mm base.

name: Water Retention, 0.06 Bar, Cores
description: 0.06 bar water, cores is the gravimetric percent water in soil core after equilibration at 0.06 bar water tension. It is reported on a <2 mm base.

name: Water Retention, 1 Bar, <2mm Clod
description: 1 bar water, clods, <2mm is the gravimetric percent water in natural fabric (clods) after equilibration at one bar water tension. It is reported on a <2 mm base.

name: Water Retention, 1 Bar, <2mm Sieve, Air-dry
description: 1 bar water, <2mm sieved, airdry is the gravimetric water content of <2 mm sieved air dry samples after equilibration at 1 bar water tension. It is reported on a <2 mm base.

name: Water Retention, 1 Bar, Cores
description: 1 bar water, cores is the gravimetric percent water in soil core after equilibration at 1 bar water tension. It is reported on a <2 mm base.

name: Water Retention, 1/10 Bar, <2mm Clod
description: 1/10 bar water, clods is the gravimetric percent water retained at 1/10 bar tension. It is measured on natural fabric (clods), and reported on a <2 mm base.

name: Water Retention, 1/10 Bar, <2mm Sieve, Air-dry
description: 1/10 bar water, <2mm fraction is the gravimetric water content of air dry <2 mm samples, after equilibration at 1/10 bar water tension. It is reported on a <2 mm base. In sands, this value approximates field capacity.

name: Water Retention, 1/10 Bar, Cores
description: 1/10 bar water, cores is the gravimetric percent water in soil core after equilibration at 1/10 bar water tension. It is reported on a <2 mm base.

name: Water Retention, 1/3 Bar, <2mm Clod
description: 1/3 bar water, clods is the gravimetric percent water in natural fabric (clods) after equilibration at 1/3 bar water tension. It is reported on a <2 mm base.

name: Water Retention, 1/3 Bar, <2mm Sieve
description: 1/3 bar water <2 mm sieved is the gravimetric percent water in sieved <2 mm samples after equilibration at 1/3 bar water tension. It is reported on a <2 mm base.

name: Water Retention, 1/3 Bar, Before Rewet
description: 1/3 bar water before rewet is the gravimetric percent water in clods after air drying when equilibrated at 1/3 bar water tension. It is reported on a <2 mm base.

name: Water Retention, 1/3 Bar, Cores
description: 1/3 bar water, cores is the gravimetric percent water in soil core after equilibration at 1/3 bar water tension. It is reported on a <2 mm base.

name: Water Retention, 1/3 Bar, Reconstituted, Moist
description: 1/3 bar water, reconstituted moist is the gravimetric percent water in reconstituted samples (held moist) after equilibration at 1/3 bar water tension. It is reported on a <2 mm base.

name: Water Retention, 1/3 Bar, Rewet
description: 1/3 bar water rewet is the gravimetric percent water in clods after air drying when equilibrated at 1/3 bar water tension. It is reported on a <2 mm base.

name: Water Retention, 15 Bar, <2mm,  Air-dry
description: 15 bar water on air dry soil is the gravimetric water content of <2 mm air dry samples after equilibration at 15 bars water tension. It is reported on a <2 mm base. The value is influenced by clay %, mineralogy, and organic carbon %.

name: Water Retention, 2 Bar, <2mm Sieve, Air-dry
description: 2 bar water, <2mm sieved, airdry is the gravimetric percent water in <2 mm airdry sieved samples after equilibration at 2 bars water tension. It is reported on a <2 mm base.

name: Water Retention, 2 Bar, Cores
description: 2 bar water, cores is the gravimetric percent water in soil core after equilibration at 2 bar water tension. It is reported on a <2 mm base.

name: Water Retention, 5 Bar, <2mm Sieve, Air-dry
description: 5 bar water, <2mm sieved, airdry is the gravimetric percent water in <2 mm airdry sieved samples after equilibration at 2 bars water tension. It is reported on a <2 mm base.

name: Weight Fraction, 0.05-0.1mm, Clay-Free <2mm
description: The gravimetric percent of particles with 0.05-0.10 mm diameter (very fine sand), reported on a clay free <2 mm base.

name: Weight per Unit Volume,  @ 15 Bar, <2mm
description: Bulk density, <2 mm fraction, 15 bar is the weight per unit volume of the <2 mm fraction, with volume being measured after equilibration at 15 bars water tension. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter on a <2 mm base.

name: Weight per Unit Volume, @ 1/3 Bar, <2mm
description: The moist weight (weight of solids and water at 1/3 bar tension) per unit volume, reported as grams per cubic centimeter on a <2 mm base.

name: Weight per Unit Volume, @ 1/3 Bar, Whole Soil
description: Bulk density, whole soil, 1/3 bar is the weight per unit volume of the soil, with volume being measured after equilibration at 1/3 bar water tension. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter on a whole soil base.

name: Weight per Unit Volume, Ovendry, Whole Soil
description: Bulk density, whole soil, oven dry is the weight per unit volume of the whole soil, with volume measured on oven dry natural fabric (clods). It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter on a whole soil base.

name: Weight per Unit Volume, Saturated, <2mm
description: The bulk density of saturated <2 mm fraction is calculated from the bulk density and water content at 1/3 bar water tension, and the amount of water needed to saturate the 1/3 bar soil. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter on a <2 mm base.

name: Weight per Unit Volume, Saturated, Whole Soil
description: The bulk density of saturated whole soil is calculated from the bulk density and water content at 1/3 bar water tension, and the amount of water needed to saturate the 1/3 bar soil. It is reported as grams per cubic centimeter on a whole soil base.

name: Weight Percentage,  2 to 5 mm, Whole Soil
description: The gravimetric percentage of 2 to 5 mm diameter particles is reported on a whole soil base.

name: Weight Percentage, <0.002mm, Clay-Free Whole Soil
description: The gravimetric percent of particles with <0.002 mm diameter (total clay), reported on a clay free whole soil base.

name: Weight Percentage, <2mm, <75mm

name: Weight Percentage, <2mm, Whole Soil

name: Weight Percentage, >2mm, Clay-Free Whole Soil

name: Weight Percentage, 0.1-0.25mm, Clay-Free <2mm

name: Weight Percentage, 0.1-75mm, 75 mm

name: Weight Percentage, 0.25-0.5mm, Clay-Free <2mm

name: Weight Percentage, 0.5-1mm, Clay-Free <2mm

name: Weight Percentage, 1-2mm, Clay-Free <2mm

name: Weight Percentage, 2 to 75 mm, Whole Soil

name: Weight Percentage, 2-20mm, Clay-Free Whole Soil

name: Weight Percentage, 2-75mm, Clay-Free Whole Soil
description: The gravimetric percent of particles with 2.0-75 mm diameter, reported on a clay free whole soil base.

name: Weight Percentage, 20 to 75 mm, Whole Soil
description: The gravimetric percentage of 20 to 75 mm diameter particles is reported on a whole soil base.

name: Weight Percentage, 250 mm and Greater, Whole Soil
description: The gravimetric percentage of >250 mm diameter particles is reported on a whole soil base.

name: Weight Percentage, 5 to 20 mm, Whole Soil
description: The gravimetric percentage of 5 to 20 mm diameter particles is reported on a whole soil base.

name: Weight Percentage, 75 to 2  mm, <75mm
description: The gravimetric percentage of 2 to 75 mm diameter particles is reported on a <75 mm base.

name: Weight Percentage, 75 to 250 mm, Whole Soil
description: The gravimetric percentage of 75 to 250 mm diameter particles is reported on a whole soil base.

name: Weight, >75mm
description: The weight of coarse fragments sieved after air-drying which are > 75 mm.

name: Weight, 2-5mm
description: The weight of the sieved coarse fragments after air-drying which are 2 to 5 mm.

name: Weight, 2-5mm, preslaked
description: The weight of the subsample, 2 to 5 mm, before slaking.

name: Weight, 2-5mm, slaked
description: The weight of the 2 to 5 mm aggregates remaining after slaking.

name: Weight, 20-75mm
description: The weight of coarse fragments sieved after air-drying which are 20 to 75 mm.

name: Weight, 5-20mm
description: The weight of the sieved coarse fragments after air-drying which are 5 to 20 mm.

name: Weight, air-dry sample
description: The weight of the air-dry bulk sample before any other processing occurs.

name: Weight, moist sample
description: The weight of the bulk sample used to prepare the air-dried sample.  This weight may be different from the self moist weight, because a subsample may have been taken for a moist preparation.

name: Weight, shelf sample
description: The pre-processed weight of the bulk sample, before any preparation work is done.  The value of this weight is used in lieu of the actual field moist sample weight to make estimates of field moisture.

name: Weight, sub-sample air-dry
description: The weight of the air-dry bulk sample after removal of clods and/or natural fabric and before any other processing occurs.

name: Weighted Particles, 0.1-75mm, 75 mm Base
description: Weighted average for the gravimetric percentage of 0.1 to 75 mm diameter particles is reported on a <75 mm base at specific depths. Silty families have <15%, loamy families >= 15%.

name: Yttrium, X-Ray Flourescence Element
description: Yttrium as determined using portable X-Ray fluorescence on a powdered sample; XRF sample cup with polypropylene film.

name: Zinc, Element Mehlich3 Extractable

name: Zinc, Total
description: Total Zn is the zinc measured after total dissolution of a size fraction of soil material. It is stored and reported as milligrams per kilogram on the base of the size fraction used.

name: Zinc, Trace Element
description: Total Zn is the zinc measured after total dissolution of a size fraction of soil material. It is stored and reported as milligrams per kilogram on the base of the size fraction used.

name: Zinc, Water Element
description: Total Zn is the zinc measured in the water sample.

name: Zinc, Water Extractable
description: The zinc extracted by the Water solution.
